# Chapolito layout (home + overlay case studies)

Use the site's existing layout system. Do not introduce Tailwind, a CSS build step, or a second global stylesheet for the home page.

## Home page shell

```html
<div class="stage" id="stage">
  <section class="home-portfolio" id="portfolio">
    <main class="grid grid--bulge" id="grid"></main>
  </section>
</div>
<aside class="dock">…</aside>
<aside class="reader" id="reader">…</aside>
```

Match `index.html` and sibling generated routes (`/{project-id}/`, `/about/`) before inventing structure.

## Stylesheets

| Area | Sheets |
|------|--------|
| Home grid + dock | `tokens.css`, `home.css`, `bento-bulge.css`, `dock.css` |
| Overlay reader / case studies | `project.css`, `detail-view.css` (+ home sheets above) |
| About overlay | `about.css` (+ home sheets above) |

Case study content is rendered into `.reader` from `javascripts/projects.js` — not standalone HTML pages.

## Grid (home bento)

- Container: `.grid.grid--bulge` inside `.home-portfolio`
- Tile placement: `data-id` selectors in `bento-bulge.css` / `home.css`
- Spacing tokens: `--pad`, `--dock-h`, `--overlay-content-top` in `tokens.css` / `detail-view.css`

## Breakpoints (common in modular sheets)

| Query | Typical use |
|-------|-------------|
| `600px` | Mobile single-column bento |
| `768px` | Tablet / about inline layout |
| `900px` | Detail split stack |
| `1200px` | Desktop artboard insets |

When editing, match surrounding units in the file you are changing.

## When classes are not enough

- Add scoped rules in the relevant modular sheet (`home.css`, `bento-bulge.css`, `detail-view.css`, `about.css`).
- Use existing tokens (`--pad`, type scales in `tokens.css`) instead of magic pixel margins.

## Avoid

- Inline `style` for layout/spacing
- A new global stylesheet for the home page
- Reading entire stylesheets when grep + a sibling section suffices
